# StudyForge Changelog

Development history of StudyForge AI.

---

# v1.0 — Initial AI Tutor Prototype

## Added

- Streamlit-based interface
- AI chat functionality
- Groq API integration
- Basic prompt system
- AI-generated responses

## Technology

- Python
- Streamlit
- Groq API


## Goal

Create a simple AI tutor prototype that could answer student questions.

---

# v1.1 — Structured Tutor Responses

## Improved

- AI prompt structure
- Tutor behaviour
- Response formatting

## Added

Rules for the AI:

- Answer directly first
- Avoid unnecessary confirmation questions
- Match explanation length to difficulty
- Teach step-by-step when needed


## Goal

Make the AI behave more like a tutor instead of a general chatbot.

---

# v1.2 — Subject Detection System

## Added

Automatic subject detection.

Subjects:

- Mathematics
- Physics
- Chemistry
- Biology
- Computer Science
- English
- History
- Geography
- Economics
- Social Science
- General


## Improvement

The AI could adjust responses based on the detected subject.

---

# v1.3 — Learning Controls

## Added

Learning depth selection:

- Quick
- Balanced
- Deep Dive
- Expert


Learning modes:

- Normal
- Exam Prep
- Hint Mode
- Concept Builder


## Goal

Allow students to control how explanations are delivered.

---

# v1.4 — Chat Storage System

## Added

SQLite database.

Stored:

- chat sessions
- messages
- conversation history


## Added

Chat management:

- New chat
- View previous chats
- Delete chats


## Goal

Move from temporary conversations to persistent learning sessions.

---

# v1.5 — Better User Experience

## Improved

- Chat-style interface
- Message styling
- Sidebar navigation
- Subject display


## Added

Custom UI styling:

- user message cards
- AI message cards


---

# v1.6 — Deployment Version

## Added

Public deployment.

Live application:

https://studyforge.streamlit.app


## Focus

Making StudyForge accessible outside local development.

---

# v1.7 — Current Foundation Version

## Added

Project documentation:

- README
- Development journey
- Architecture notes
- Roadmap
- Engineering decisions


## Improved

- Cleaner project organisation
- Better AI tutor instructions
- More product-focused direction


## Current Stack

Frontend:
- Streamlit

Backend:
- Python

AI:
- Groq API

Database:
- SQLite


---

# Known Limitations

Current version still needs:

- Context-aware conversations
- User accounts
- Student profiles
- Weakness tracking
- Progress dashboard
- Quiz generation
- RAG with notes/textbooks


---

# Future Development

## v1.8

Context upgrade:

- Previous messages sent to AI
- Better follow-up questions


## v1.9

Personalisation:

- User accounts
- Student profiles
- Learning preferences


## v2.0

Learning system:

- Weakness tracking
- Progress analytics
- Quiz generation


## v2.5+

Knowledge system:

- Notes upload
- Textbook retrieval
- RAG


## Future Architecture

- React + Tailwind CSS frontend
- FastAPI backend
- PostgreSQL database


---

# Reflection

StudyForge started as a small AI tutor experiment.

While building it, I learned that a useful AI application is not only about the model.

The important parts are:

- user experience
- data management
- system design
- continuous improvement
